<h2> Meloni, "reaffirmed democratic values denied by fascism"
"Today Italy celebrates the 80th Anniversary of Liberation. On this day, the nation honors its rediscovered freedom > and reaffirms the centrality of those democratic values which the fascist regime had denied and which for seventy-seven years have been engraved in the Republican Constitution." So Premier Meloni, in a passage of the statement diffused by Palazzo Chigi.
