Jews of the Resistance
Fadlun recalled among others Bruno Dell'Ariccia>, who escaped the retata of 16 October, which joined the partisans in Tivoli. Alberto Terracina>, in the Resistance of the Roman Castles, which fought between Genzano, Lanuvio and Velletri, until the liberation of Rome. Piero Cividalli>: In 1939, he fled Italy with the family for racial laws. At age 19, he volunteered in the British Army. He trained in Egypt, ready to return to his land to fight the Nazis. His face has long been that of the last Italian survivor of the Jewish Brigade >. The Jewish Brigade that landed in Naples in September 1943, building hospitals and giving refuge to refugees. That entered Rome in June '44 with the star of David> sewn on the uniform. From the Ferramonti camp to Milan, Aaron HaKodesh>. No one can take away the freedom to honor them. To tell, explain, remember. And we remember well >!” he concluded.
&nbsp;
<h2> Defense of Memory and anti-Semitism today</h2>
“The 25th April> is this – Fadlun explained –. It is memory. It is grateful > It is identities. It is to say thanks to partisans, Jews and not. Americans, allies. To the righteous. To those who defended human lives at the cost of their own. But today on 25 April is also a border. After October 7, we saw the emergence of anti-Semitism. On walls, in social, in squares, even in institutions. Suspect is followed by pain > and horror > At pogrom>, loneliness. But we do not return.» We do not accept ambiguity. We do not confuse executioners and victims. We do not allow memory > to be distorted or instrumentalized. Or, worse, overturned and used against us” – he continued – “We strengthen the forces of order >, institutions >, who protects our rights every day. Who is close not only when it is easy, but when it is right>. Because we are the Jews of Rome.» And let us not forget anything.» We'll be there every 25 April. Face uncovered. Head high. Without hiding, without being afraid to be what we are. United for freedom >!” he concluded.
<h2> The final question by Fadlun</h2>
"From our side I see the flags of Italy waving because we are Italian fairs". On the other hand – Fadlun has specified – I see to wind up the Palestinian flags>. Are these gentlemen Italian or Palestinian? There's no one in Italy. What are they celebrating?> It seems to me a false historian.»
<h2>Gualtieri, "to keep alive the memory of a fundamental page of our history"</h2>
"Eighty years ago, on April 25, 1945, Italy regained freedom. > We remember with deep gratitude the sacrifice and determination of those women and men who fought against Nazi fascism and redeemed the country." So on Instagram the mayor of Rome, Roberto&nbsp;Gualtieri. "Rome, city Gold Medal for Resistance >- remembers - today honors the memory of all those who fought to deliver us a free and democratic Italy. Their example still guides us today in our daily commitment to defend and promote the fundamental principles of our Republic: freedom, democracy, social justice and equality in rights. We keep alive> the memory of that fundamental page of our history, turning it into inspiration to defend those achievements and build together a better future. Happy Liberation Day to all!" concludes the mayor &nbsp;Gualtieri.
