AGI - On its website, the Vatican lists the 76-year-old Cardinal Angelo Becciu> as a "non-elector", uniting it to those who reached the age of 80. Becciu, speaking with Reuters, confirmed that the Vatican list of unelegible cardinals "has no legal value", that there was no "some explicit will" to exclude it from the Conclave and that it has never been asked to formally renounce the privilege in writing.
&nbsp;
In addition, Becciu stressed that he had met Pope Francis in January last, before the reconstruction in February, and the Pontiff would have told him to be close to a solution.
&nbsp;
"I think I have found a solution", the words of Francis, quoted by the Cardinal. "They will be my cardinal brothers to decide," concluded the Sardinian cardinal, referring to the meetings of the Congregations that are taking place these days.&nbsp;

