The Sistine Chapel will be closed to the public from Monday 28 April "for the needs of the Conclave". The Holy See makes it known. "All visits to the Vatican Gardens and the Necropolis of the Via Triumphalis are also suspended." The Direction of Museums and Cultural Heritage, "in expressing deep mourning and pain for the disappearance of the Holy Father", we read, that Saturday, 26 April, "the Vatican Museums and the Museums of Castel Gandolfo will be closed to the public, as a sign of mourning, for the funerals of the Roman Pontiff Francis".
